---
description: Quality, release, and operational safety rules
alwaysApply: true
---

- Run the narrowest meaningful tests after changes.
- Do not weaken tests, lint rules, or type checks to make a change pass.
- For config, env, auth, payment, infra, or database changes, include rollback notes.
- For schema migrations, separate migration safety from feature logic when feasible.
- Favor observability: logs, errors, and key metrics should make failures diagnosable.
- Treat preview validation as required for UI-affecting work.
- Ship only when Definition of Done is satisfied.
